<subSubSection pageId="75" pageNumber="76" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="75" pageNumber="76">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="75" pageNumber="76">
This genus is concentrated in eastern and southern Brazil, with one species- 
<taxonomicName class="Gastropoda" family="Simpulopsidae" genus="Simpulopsis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Simpulopsis (Eudioptus) citrinovitrea" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="75" pageNumber="76" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="citrinovitrea" subGenus="Eudioptus">Simpulopsis (Eudioptus) citrinovitrea</taxonomicName>
(S. Moricand, 1836)-extending in several Andean countries with a remarkable disjunct distribution. 
<bibRefCitation author="Cuezzo, MG" journalOrPublisher="Malacologia" pageId="85" pageNumber="86" pagination="135 - 191" title="Species catalogue of Orthalicoidea in Argentina (Gastropoda: Stylommatophora)." url="10.4002/040.056.0210" volume="56" year="2013">Cuezzo et al. (2013)</bibRefCitation>
also mentioned the occurrence in 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“Chile”">&quot;Chile&quot;</normalizedToken>
for 
<taxonomicName class="Gastropoda" family="Simpulopsidae" genus="Simpulopsis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Simpulopsis (Eudioptus) eudioptus" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="75" pageNumber="76" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="eudioptus" subGenus="Eudioptus">Simpulopsis (Eudioptus) eudioptus</taxonomicName>
(Ihering in Pilsbry, 1897), however, without further evidence.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
